pros:
- Flexible timetable ;
- Salary;
- Friendly colleagues;

- Friendly atmosphere, almost like a 2nd family;
- People engagement in various teams, such as Voice Insight Action, Social Committee, Training Team, CSR, so anyone with an idea, can implement it and it will make a change;
- Various fields you can work in, from Pricing to Order Management or Contracts team, Compliance and so on;
- Good positioning, the offices are in Pipera, where you can find: Mega Image, various restaurants (from healthy food, to sandwiches or pizza, fresh barbeque etc), various banks, pharmacy, beauty salon etc
- Work from Home is a great advantage, flexi program also available in some teams (the program could be from 08:00 - 17:00, 09:00 - 18:00 or 10:00 - 19:00), and no one will force you to stay extra hours, only if you really want to gain extra money or a day off;

cons:
Crazy working hours when in a global role; difficult to do work life balance;
Overtime not paid and officially not encourage but everyone expects you to do it;
You don’t progress unless you do "walk the extra mile" i.e. overtime;
Very cumbersome processes, it takes ages to get things approved; Lots of admin work
HR have very strict rules; you have to fight with them for every 1% salary increase you want to give to an employee, very limited as a manager to what you can do for bonuses, salary increase or other benefits for your team

pros:
